<p><b>Rasterization</b> or <b>Rasterisation</b> is the task of taking an image described in a <a href="/wiki/Vector_graphics" title="Vector graphics">vector graphics</a> format (shapes) and converting it into a <a href="/wiki/Raster_image" title="Raster image" class="mw-redirect">raster image</a> (<a href="/wiki/Pixel" title="Pixel">pixels</a> or dots) for output on a <a href="/wiki/Computer_display" title="Computer display" class="mw-redirect">video display</a> or <a href="/wiki/Computer_printer" title="Computer printer" class="mw-redirect">printer</a>, or for storage in a bitmap file format.</p>
